SIMPLE: sabellian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sabellian
<hw>Sa*bel"li*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to the
doctrines or tenets of Sabellius. See <er>Sabellian</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sabellian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sabellian
<hw>Sa*bel"li*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A follower of <etsep>Sabellius</etsep>, a presbyter of
Ptolemais in the third century, who maintained that there is but one
person in the Godhead, and that the Son and Holy Spirit are only
different powers, operations, or offices of the one God the
Father.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sabellianism</ent>⟦br⟧
